{"id": "EUVD-2025-32268", "enisaUuid": "0de7f454-ff1b-3298-8fb4-f309d05d3dc0", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/ksm: fix race with VMA iteration and mm_struct teardown\n\nexit_mmap() will tear down the VMAs and maple tree with the mmap_lock held\nin write mode.  Ensure that the maple tree is still valid by checking\nksm_test_exit() after taking the mmap_lock in read mode, but before the\nfor_each_vma() iterator dereferences a destroyed maple tree.\n\nSince the maple tree is destroyed, the flags telling lockdep to check an\nexternal lock has been cleared.  Skip the for_each_vma() iterator to avoid\ndereferencing a maple tree without the external lock flag, which would\ncreate a lockdep warning.", "datePublished": "2025-10-04T15:44:21", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-04T15:44:21", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53614", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/286b0cab31bac29960e5684f6fb331d42f03b363", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6db504ce55bdbc575723938fc480713c9183f6a2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b4f664ffd8f78c05a1fd542a28bc5a11e994c014"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53614", "GHSA-m8wv-9hr6-j68w"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1913366a-5069-354d-a899-8d3451e60afc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a5f18ba0727656bd1fe3bcdb0d563f81790f9a04 <6db504ce55bdbc575723938fc480713c9183f6a2"}, {"id": "2fc37c64-0cad-332a-8de0-d4a9bf709f84", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3ac5dfb3-42af-3b82-bea4-e5eb7da4caa9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a5f18ba0727656bd1fe3bcdb0d563f81790f9a04 <b4f664ffd8f78c05a1fd542a28bc5a11e994c014"}, {"id": "45eb9272-6602-38e3-b47a-5a676400235e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.22"}, {"id": "9aa5d784-de73-3624-ba23-ebda5d37a23f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.1"}, {"id": "a64f678f-a03e-3a35-90ac-6fc215533ff3",